OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,FA mother from Telford who fractured
OL,7,Fher seven-week-old daughter's skull,
OL,8,Fcausing injuries which contributed to
OL,9,Fher death more than two years later,
OL,10,Fhas been jailed for life.
OL,12,FSarah Ngaba, 32, accepted that she
OL,13,Fcaused "dreadful, life-shortening and
OL,14,Flife-limiting" head injuries to Eliza
OL,15,FNgaba, but denied murder, claiming she
OL,16,Fwas instead guilty of infanticide.
OL,18,FShe was sentenced to a minimum of 19
OL,19,Fyears, reduced to 12 years, to reflect
OL,20,Fthe time spent in custody to date.
OL,26,@uD@HOUvD@NO]
