OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,FNgaba, from Briarwood in Telford, was
OL,7,Fpreviously convicted at Birmingham
OL,8,FCrown Court in November 2020, of
OL,9,Fcausing grievous bodily harm to her
OL,10,Fchild, who was left profoundly
OL,11,Fdisabled by the assault.
OL,13,FShe was charged with murder after
OL,14,FEliza died aged two in August 2022
OL,15,Ffrom a respiratory infection, having
OL,16,Fbeen left vulnerable by the assault in
OL,17,FNovember 2019.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,FEliza's injuries were caused by
OL,7,Fforceful shaking "together with a very
OL,8,Fsignificant impact" to the head,
OL,9,Fcausing a complex skull fracture.
OL,11,FAn earlier court hearing was told
OL,12,FNgaba took a bath and bought a lottery
OL,13,Fticket from a shop before taking Eliza
OL,14,Fto hospital in a taxi on 13 November
OL,15,F2019.
OL,17,FA witness who saw Eliza on a video
OL,18,Fcall on the morning of the assault
OL,19,F"could see that her body was shaking".
OL,26,@oD@ROUpD@SO]{D@AOU{D@eO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,FThe man advised Ngaba to take Eliza to
OL,7,Fhospital immediately, but the
OL,8,Fdefendant said she needed to have a
OL,9,Fbath and did not call an ambulance.
OL,11,FDoorbell footage caught Ngaba leaving
OL,12,Fher flat at 8.40am, and footage from a
OL,13,Flocal supermarket at 8.59am showed her
OL,14,Fbuying a lottery ticket and obtaining
OL,15,Fcashback.
OL,17,FThe taxi driver arrived at 9.05am and
OL,18,Fdescribed the defendant as being very
OL,19,Fcalm and not seeming worried.
OL,21,F"Eliza loved cuddles"
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,FIn a statement Eliza'a foster parents
OL,7,FLaura Haynes and Gary said:
OL,9,F"Eliza completely stole our hearts...
OL,10,Fwe gained Eliza's complete trust, she
OL,11,Fwould coo for our attention...
OL,12,Fnaturally a content baby.
OL,14,F'She had a way of stealing the hearts
OL,15,Fof those who were fortunate enough to
OL,16,Fmeet her...' loved the theme tune to
OL,17,FThe Chase, and dipping her feet in the
OL,18,Fsea... 'Above all, Eliza loved
OL,19,Fcuddles.'
OL,26,@qD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,F'Our time with Eliza was too short ...
OL,7,Fwe love her dearly and miss her
OL,8,Fterribly every day".
OL,10,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,11,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,12,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,13,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,15,F"You have never shown remorse"
OL,17,FSentencing Ngaba, Mrs Justice Brunner
OL,18,FKC said:
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,F"You brutally assaulted her on 13th
OL,7,FNovember 2019 when she was just 7
OL,8,Fweeks old.
OL,10,F"At times she experienced three or
OL,11,Ffour seizures each day....
OL,13,F"Eliza was so fortunate that after her
OL,14,Fterrible start to life, the Haynes'
OL,15,Ffamily embraced her.....
OL,17,F"Nothing that I can do can compensate
OL,18,Ffor that loss...
OL,26,@rD@AOUuD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,FShe continued: "You deliberately
OL,7,Fdelayed and you deliberately concealed
OL,8,FEliza's state.
OL,10,F"It is clear you did not maximise her
OL,11,Fchances by seeking help and telling
OL,12,Fdoctors what you had done to her.
OL,14,F"This was not a brief loss of control,
OL,15,Fyou not only shook her with such
OL,16,Fviolence that you caused bleeding, but
OL,17,Falso struck her head on a hard
OL,18,Fsurface...
OL,20,F"You may have regretted what you did
OL,21,Fbut you have never shown remorse.
OL,26,@nD@POUrD@AOUvD@AOU|D@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,F"You are a person who loses her temper
OL,7,Fand lashes out."
OL,9,F"A defenceless baby"
OL,11,FKate Seal from the Crown Prosecution
OL,12,FService said:
OL,14,F"This is one of the most distressing
OL,15,Fcases I have encountered in my eight
OL,16,Fyears as a prosecutor. Eliza was just
OL,17,Fseven weeks old, entirely defenceless,
OL,18,Fand dependent on her mother for care
OL,19,Fand protection.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@PO]vD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,F"Sarah Ngaba inflicted catastrophic
OL,7,Finjuries on a defenceless baby and
OL,8,Fthen did everything she could to avoid
OL,9,Fresponsibility for what she had done.
OL,11,F"Her account changed repeatedly and in
OL,12,Fways that served only her own
OL,13,Finterests.
OL,15,F"She initially blamed a walking stick,
OL,16,Fthen Eliza's father, and when phone
OL,17,Frecords and CCTV proved that was
OL,18,Fimpossible, she changed her account
OL,19,Fagain.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G10/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1781453488
OL,3,CMother who fractured baby's skull
OL,4,Cleaving her disabled, jailed for life
OL,6,F"Eliza should have been safe in her
OL,7,Fmother's care. Instead, her life was
OL,8,Firrevocably damaged and, ultimately,
OL,9,Fcut short.
OL,11,F"Our thoughts remain with all those
OL,12,Fwho loved her."
OL,26,@tD@OO]
